I’ve converged on a runtime-only PoC design: discover live routers on-chain, buy a candidate fee-on-transfer token with temporary WETH, invoke `routerCall` with a generic forwarding payload that pulls `amountIn` from the proxy, and only keep the attempt if the proxy’s post-call balance falls below its pre-call balance. I’m replacing the current verifier with that scanner now and then I’ll compile it locally.
codex
I’m writing the replacement verifier now. It will self-discover routers and token balances at runtime, attempt the exact fee-on-transfer shortfall path first with any assets it already holds, and only then fall back to temporary WETH funding.
